---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro'
---

<Layout title="About — BounceProof.io">
  <SiteHeader />
  <main class="pt-14">
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-12 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">About</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-gray-400">More coming soon.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pb-24">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white text-center tracking-tight">What is a canary?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-400 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        A canary is a deadline you set on a workflow instead of a log line you hope to see. You start one the moment
        a workflow kicks off, and resolve it the moment that workflow actually finishes — no matter how many systems
        it passes through in between. If the canary doesn't resolve before its deadline, <span class="text-green-500 font-semibold">BounceProof</span>
        knows the workflow is late or stuck, even if every individual system along the way reported success.
      </p>

      <svg viewBox="0 0 940 400" class="mt-10 w-full block mx-auto" role="img">
        <title>A canary created and resolved around a multi-system workflow</title>
        <desc>A workflow passes through Order Service, Payment Service, and Fulfillment Service in sequence. Order Service calls the BounceProof Engine to create a canary when the workflow starts, and Fulfillment Service calls the BounceProof Engine to resolve that same canary when the workflow finishes.</desc>
        <defs>
          <marker id="arrowGray3" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" orient="auto-start-reverse">
            <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9ca3af" />
          </marker>
          <marker id="arrowGreen3" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" orient="auto-start-reverse">
            <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#22c55e" />
          </marker>
        </defs>

        <text x="470" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#9ca3af">One canary tracks the whole workflow, regardless of how many systems it touches</text>

        <!-- Workflow systems -->
        <g>
          <rect x="20" y="45" width="260" height="100" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="150" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="19" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">Order Service</text>
          <text x="150" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#9ca3af">workflow starts</text>
        </g>
        <line x1="280" y1="95" x2="330" y2="95" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowGray3)"/>
        <g>
          <rect x="330" y="45" width="260" height="100" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="460" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="19" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">Payment Service</text>
          <text x="460" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#9ca3af">charge processed</text>
        </g>
        <line x1="590" y1="95" x2="640" y2="95" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowGray3)"/>
        <g>
          <rect x="640" y="45" width="260" height="100" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="770" y="87" text-anchor="middle" font-size="19" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">Fulfillment Service</text>
          <text x="770" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#9ca3af">workflow finishes</text>
        </g>

        <!-- BounceProof Engine -->
        <g>
          <rect x="330" y="280" width="280" height="100" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="470" y="322" text-anchor="middle" font-size="19" font-weight="600" fill="#4ade80">BounceProof Engine</text>
          <text x="470" y="348" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#9ca3af">tracks the canary</text>
        </g>

        <!-- Create call: Order Service -> Engine -->
        <path d="M 150 145 L 150 210 L 410 210 L 410 280" fill="none" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowGreen3)"/>
        <rect x="190" y="170" width="180" height="32" rx="6" fill="#0f1f17" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="280" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">create canary</text>

        <!-- Resolve call: Fulfillment Service -> Engine -->
        <path d="M 770 145 L 770 210 L 530 210 L 530 280" fill="none" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrowGreen3)"/>
        <rect x="560" y="170" width="180" height="32" rx="6" fill="#0f1f17" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="650" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">resolve canary</text>
      </svg>
    </section>

    <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pb-24">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white text-center tracking-tight">How a verifier works</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-400 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        By default, <span class="text-green-500 font-semibold">BounceProof</span> trusts the caller — resolving a canary
        is as simple as telling us it's done. A verifier raises the bar: it lets you attach workflow-specific logic
        that runs before a resolution is accepted, so "reported in" and "actually correct" aren't treated as the same thing.
      </p>
      <ol class="mt-10 space-y-12">
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="flex-none w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/40 text-green-500 font-semibold flex items-center justify-center">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg">Configure it on a canary type</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm max-w-2xl">
              Point a canary type at a verifier endpoint you control — a small HTTP service that knows what
              "successful" means for that specific workflow.
            </p>
            <svg viewBox="0 0 800 500" class="mt-6 w-full max-w-2xl block mx-auto" role="img">
              <title>Canary editor page showing verifier configuration</title>
              <desc>A canary editor form for the canary type "order-completion-webhook" with a "Use a Verifier" checkbox checked, revealing a URL field set to https://api.mysite.com/canary-verify/order-completion-webhook</desc>
              <rect x="0" y="0" width="800" height="500" rx="14" fill="#111827" stroke="#374151" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <text x="32" y="56" font-size="28" font-weight="700" fill="#ffffff">Edit Canary Type</text>
              <line x1="32" y1="76" x2="768" y2="76" stroke="#374151" stroke-width="1"/>
              <text x="32" y="116" font-size="16" font-weight="600" fill="#9ca3af">CANARY TYPE</text>
              <rect x="32" y="124" width="736" height="56" rx="8" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <text x="48" y="160" font-size="20" fill="#ffffff" font-family="monospace">order-completion-webhook</text>
              <text x="32" y="212" font-size="16" font-weight="600" fill="#9ca3af">TIMEOUT (HH:MM:SS)</text>
              <rect x="32" y="220" width="228" height="56" rx="8" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <text x="146" y="256" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#ffffff" font-family="monospace">00</text>
              <text x="270" y="256" font-size="20" fill="#6b7280" font-family="monospace">:</text>
              <rect x="282" y="220" width="228" height="56" rx="8" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <text x="396" y="256" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#ffffff" font-family="monospace">00</text>
              <text x="520" y="256" font-size="20" fill="#6b7280" font-family="monospace">:</text>
              <rect x="532" y="220" width="204" height="56" rx="8" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <text x="634" y="256" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#ffffff" font-family="monospace">00</text>
              <rect x="32" y="300" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#22c55e"/>
              <path d="M38 314 L46 321 L56 305" stroke="#0b1f12" stroke-width="3.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <text x="76" y="321" font-size="20" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">Use a Verifier</text>
              <text x="32" y="368" font-size="16" font-weight="600" fill="#9ca3af">VERIFIER URL</text>
              <rect x="32" y="376" width="736" height="56" rx="8" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <text x="48" y="412" font-size="16" fill="#ffffff" font-family="monospace">https://api.mysite.com/canary-verify/order-completion-webhook</text>
              <text x="32" y="464" font-size="16" fill="#9ca3af">BounceProof will POST the canary's metadata to this URL before resolving it</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="flex-none w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/40 text-green-500 font-semibold flex items-center justify-center">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg">Resolution triggers the call</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm max-w-2xl">
              When the workflow calls back to resolve its canary, BounceProof doesn't mark it healthy right away.
              It first calls your verifier, passing along the canary's metadata — the same JSON payload you
              attached when the canary was created.
            </p>
            <svg viewBox="0 0 920 850" class="mt-6 w-full" role="img">
              <title>Canary expiry triggers a verifier call, which checks WooCommerce and responds</title>
              <desc>After 5 minutes with no resolution, the canary expires. BounceProof's engine calls the verifier on the customer's internal API, and the verifier calls the WooCommerce API to get the order status before sending a response back to the engine.</desc>
              <defs>
                <marker id="arrowGray2" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                  <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9ca3af" />
                </marker>
                <marker id="arrowGreen2" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                  <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#22c55e" />
                </marker>
              </defs>

              <g>
                <rect x="20" y="20" width="700" height="110" rx="10" fill="rgba(234,179,8,0.14)" stroke="#eab308" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="370" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="26" font-weight="600" fill="#facc15">Canary: PENDING</text>
                <text x="370" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">no resolution yet</text>
              </g>
              <line x1="370" y1="130" x2="370" y2="180" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGray2)"/>
              <text x="400" y="160" font-size="18" fill="#9ca3af">5 min</text>

              <g>
                <rect x="20" y="180" width="700" height="110" rx="10" fill="rgba(239,68,68,0.14)" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="370" y="225" text-anchor="middle" font-size="26" font-weight="600" fill="#f87171">Canary: EXPIRED</text>
                <text x="370" y="258" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">timeout reached</text>
              </g>
              <line x1="370" y1="290" x2="370" y2="340" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGray2)"/>

              <g>
                <rect x="20" y="340" width="700" height="120" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="370" y="388" text-anchor="middle" font-size="26" font-weight="600" fill="#4ade80">BounceProof Engine</text>
                <text x="370" y="422" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">expiry detected, calls verifier</text>
              </g>
              <line x1="370" y1="460" x2="370" y2="510" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGray2)"/>
              <text x="400" y="490" font-size="18" fill="#9ca3af">calls verifier</text>

              <g>
                <rect x="20" y="510" width="700" height="120" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="370" y="558" text-anchor="middle" font-size="24" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">Verifier (your internal API)</text>
                <text x="370" y="592" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">asked to confirm the order</text>
              </g>
              <line x1="370" y1="630" x2="370" y2="680" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGray2)"/>
              <text x="400" y="660" font-size="18" fill="#9ca3af">checks WooCommerce</text>

              <g>
                <rect x="20" y="680" width="700" height="110" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="370" y="725" text-anchor="middle" font-size="24" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">WooCommerce API</text>
                <text x="370" y="758" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">order status lookup</text>
              </g>

              <!-- Response: Verifier -> Engine -->
              <path d="M 720 565 L 800 565 L 800 400 L 720 400" fill="none" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGreen2)"/>
              <rect x="745" y="466" width="150" height="32" rx="6" fill="#0f1f17" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="1"/>
              <text x="820" y="488" text-anchor="middle" font-size="18" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">response</text>

              <text x="460" y="820" text-anchor="middle" font-size="18" fill="#9ca3af">BounceProof calls the verifier, which checks WooCommerce, then responds back to the engine</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="flex-none w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/40 text-green-500 font-semibold flex items-center justify-center">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg">Your logic decides</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm max-w-2xl">
              The verifier checks whatever actually matters — an order total matches, a payment cleared for the
              right amount, a file landed where it should — and returns a pass or fail.
            </p>
            <svg viewBox="0 0 1200 850" class="mt-6 w-full" role="img">
              <title>Canary expiry triggers verifier call, which checks WooCommerce and returns Extend, Trigger, or Resolve</title>
              <desc>After 5 minutes with no resolution, the canary expires. BounceProof's engine calls the verifier on the customer's internal API. The verifier calls the WooCommerce API to get the order status, then returns either an Extend verdict, a Trigger verdict, or a Resolve verdict back to the engine.</desc>
              <defs>
                <marker id="arrowGray4" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                  <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9ca3af" />
                </marker>
                <marker id="arrowBlue4" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                  <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#3b82f6" />
                </marker>
                <marker id="arrowRed4" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                  <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#ef4444" />
                </marker>
                <marker id="arrowGreen4" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" orient="auto-start-reverse">
                  <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#22c55e" />
                </marker>
              </defs>

              <g>
                <rect x="240" y="20" width="700" height="110" rx="10" fill="rgba(234,179,8,0.14)" stroke="#eab308" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="590" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="26" font-weight="600" fill="#facc15">Canary: PENDING</text>
                <text x="590" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">no resolution yet</text>
              </g>
              <line x1="590" y1="130" x2="590" y2="180" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGray4)"/>
              <text x="620" y="160" font-size="18" fill="#9ca3af">5 min</text>

              <g>
                <rect x="240" y="180" width="700" height="110" rx="10" fill="rgba(239,68,68,0.14)" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="590" y="225" text-anchor="middle" font-size="26" font-weight="600" fill="#f87171">Canary: EXPIRED</text>
                <text x="590" y="258" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">timeout reached</text>
              </g>
              <line x1="590" y1="290" x2="590" y2="340" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGray4)"/>

              <g>
                <rect x="240" y="340" width="700" height="120" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="590" y="388" text-anchor="middle" font-size="26" font-weight="600" fill="#4ade80">BounceProof Engine</text>
                <text x="590" y="422" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">expiry detected, calls verifier</text>
              </g>
              <line x1="590" y1="460" x2="590" y2="510" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGray4)"/>
              <text x="620" y="490" font-size="18" fill="#9ca3af">calls verifier</text>

              <g>
                <rect x="240" y="510" width="700" height="120" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="590" y="558" text-anchor="middle" font-size="24" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">Verifier (your internal API)</text>
                <text x="590" y="592" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">asked to confirm the order</text>
              </g>
              <line x1="590" y1="630" x2="590" y2="680" stroke="#9ca3af" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGray4)"/>
              <text x="620" y="660" font-size="18" fill="#9ca3af">checks WooCommerce</text>

              <g>
                <rect x="240" y="680" width="700" height="110" rx="10" fill="#1f2937" stroke="#4b5563" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <text x="590" y="725" text-anchor="middle" font-size="24" font-weight="600" fill="#ffffff">WooCommerce API</text>
                <text x="590" y="758" text-anchor="middle" font-size="20" fill="#9ca3af">order status lookup</text>
              </g>

              <!-- Extend: Verifier -> Engine -->
              <path d="M 940 545 L 1020 545 L 1020 395 L 940 395" fill="none" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowBlue4)"/>
              <rect x="955" y="454" width="150" height="32" rx="6" fill="#0f1f17" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="1"/>
              <text x="1030" y="476" text-anchor="middle" font-size="18" font-weight="700" fill="#ffffff">"Extend"</text>

              <!-- Trigger: Verifier -> Engine -->
              <path d="M 940 600 L 1090 600 L 1090 425 L 940 425" fill="none" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowRed4)"/>
              <rect x="1020" y="512" width="150" height="32" rx="6" fill="#0f1f17" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="1"/>
              <text x="1095" y="534" text-anchor="middle" font-size="18" font-weight="700" fill="#ffffff">"Trigger"</text>

              <!-- Resolve: Verifier -> Engine (left side) -->
              <path d="M 240 520 L 120 520 L 120 440 L 240 440" fill="none" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="2.5" marker-end="url(#arrowGreen4)"/>
              <rect x="30" y="464" width="180" height="32" rx="6" fill="#0f1f17" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="1"/>
              <text x="120" y="486" text-anchor="middle" font-size="18" font-weight="700" fill="#ffffff">"Resolve"</text>

              <text x="600" y="820" text-anchor="middle" font-size="18" fill="#9ca3af">"Resolve" marks it healthy; "Extend" pushes the deadline out; "Trigger" fires the alert now</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="flex-none w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green-500/10 border border-green-500/40 text-green-500 font-semibold flex items-center justify-center">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-lg">Pass or fail, you find out</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm max-w-2xl">
              A pass resolves the canary as healthy, same as if there were no verifier at all. A fail alerts you
              immediately, even though the workflow technically reported success — catching the cases where
              something completed but completed wrong.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
